<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Item&nbsp;7.01.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Regulation FD Disclosure. </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This
information will not be deemed &#147;filed&#148; for purposes of Section&nbsp;18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#147;Exchange Act&#148;), or incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of 1933, as
amended, or the Exchange Act, except as expressly set forth by specific reference in such a filing. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On September&nbsp;7, 2012, Kraft Foods
Inc. issued a press release relating to Kraft Foods Group, Inc.&#146;s presentation to analysts and investors at SeaPort Boston World Trade Center regarding Kraft Foods Group&#146;s North American grocery business following its spin-off from Kraft
Foods Inc. A copy of the press release is being furnished as Exhibit 99.1 to this Current Report on Form 8-K. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The presentation will be
available via a live audio webcast at www.kraftfoodsgroup.com. An archived rebroadcast and the presentation slides will be available for one year following the webcast. The presentation slides, including Regulation G reconciliations, used in the
presentation are being furnished as Exhibit 99.2 to this Current Report on Form 8-K. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>NON-GAAP FINANCIAL MEASURES </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods Group reports its financial results in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States (&#147;GAAP&#148;).
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods Group&#146;s top-line measure is organic revenue, which excludes the impacts of related party transactions, divestitures,
currency and accounting calendar changes. The company uses organic revenue and corresponding metrics as non-GAAP financial measures. Management believes organic revenue better reflects the underlying growth from the ongoing activities of Kraft Foods
Group&#146;s business and provides improved comparability of results. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The company also uses free cash flow as a non-GAAP financial measure.
Free cash flow is defined as net cash provided by operating activities less capital expenditures. Management believes free cash flow shows the financial health of, and how efficiently we are running, the company. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-GAAP financial measures should be viewed in addition to, and not as an alternative for, the company&#146;s results prepared in accordance with GAAP.
In addition, the non-GAAP measures the company is using may differ from the non-GAAP measures used by other companies. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top"></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>BUILDING &#147;NORTH AMERICA&#146;S BEST FOOD&nbsp;&amp; BEVERAGE COMPANY&#148; </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Kraft Foods Outlines Growth Plans for North American Grocery Business </I></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Plans to Deliver Profitable Top-Line Growth, Consistent Bottom-Line Growth and Superior Dividend Payout</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><I>Issues 2013 GAAP EPS Guidance of Approximately $2.60</I> </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">BOSTON &#150; Sept. 7, 2012 &#150; The future leadership team of Kraft Foods Inc.&#146;s North American grocery business presented its growth plans and financial outlook at a meeting of analysts and
investors today in Boston. The business, which will become an independent public company in October, expects to deliver steady and profitable top-line growth, consistent bottom-line growth and a superior dividend payout. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">As previously announced, Kraft Foods Inc. plans to spin-off Kraft Foods Group, Inc., which will hold Kraft Foods&#146; North American
grocery business, at 5 p.m. EDT on Oct. 1, 2012. Kraft Foods Group will trade on the NASDAQ stock exchange under the ticker symbol &#147;KRFT.&#148; Following the spin-off, Kraft Foods Inc. will be renamed Mondel&#275;z International, Inc.
Mondel&#275;z International will trade on the NASDAQ stock exchange under the ticker symbol &#147;MDLZ.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;Today, I
have the honor to introduce a new Kraft, one with the spirit of a startup and the soul of a powerhouse,&#148; said Tony Vernon, President of Kraft Foods North America and future Chief Executive Officer of Kraft Foods Group. &#147;Our aim is to be
North America&#146;s best food and beverage company, and we&#146;ll get there by continuing to offer products consumers love, creating a performance-based culture that motivates and excites employees and becoming the best investment in the
industry.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;Tony and his team have a clear mission and are ready to deliver,&#148; said John Cahill, future
Executive Chairman of Kraft Foods Group. &#147;I&#146;m confident we have the right plans and people in place to unlock the value of the North American grocery business after its spin-off.&#148; </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Unleashing the Power of an Unparalleled Portfolio </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods Group offers a diverse, unrivaled portfolio of admired brands with products in the beverages, cheese, convenient meals and
grocery categories. Led by iconic brands like <I>Kraft</I>, <I>Oscar Mayer</I> and <I>Maxwell House</I>, Kraft Foods Group will be North America&#146;s fourth largest consumer packaged food and beverage company out of the gate, with revenues of
approximately $19 billion in 2011. Ten of the company&#146;s brands achieved sales of $500 million or more in 2011, while an additional 17 brands posted sales of $100 million or more in 2011. Approximately 80 percent of Kraft Foods Group&#146;s
revenue comes from categories in which the company holds the No.&nbsp;1 or No.&nbsp;2 market position. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Growth Plans </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods Group&#146;s future growth will be driven by a four-part strategic plan: making its people its competitive edge, executing
with excellence, &#147;turbocharging&#148; its iconic brands and redefining efficiency. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">To <I>make its people its competitive
edge</I>, Kraft Foods Group plans to create a more nimble, less-layered organization and unleash the skills and creativity of its people by breaking down walls &#151; literally and figuratively &#151; at the company. Incentive plans will be
redesigned to incorporate stock ownership more broadly to reinforce the alignment between employee and shareholder interests. Stepped-up investment in talent acquisition and a newly created &#147;Kraft University&#148; will help create the next
generation of Kraft leaders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Second, Kraft Foods Group will <I>execute with excellence</I> by strategically allocating
resources to best leverage the breadth of the company&#146;s portfolio, sales and warehouse distribution system. In April 2012, Kraft Foods Group&#146;s highly regarded sales organization teamed up with Acosta, a leading sales agency, which has
helped expand in-store merchandising coverage by 30 percent and grow the company&#146;s presence on store shelves with a 5 percent increase in total distribution points. The sales organization has also realigned its incentives to focus on net
revenue growth and profit dollars. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The third step in the company&#146;s plan is to &#147;<I>turbocharge</I>&#148;<I> its
iconic brands</I> so they can grow faster than the market and key competitors. This means delivering the right products at the right price points, introducing &#147;big bet&#148; innovations like <I>MiO,</I> which created an entirely new product
category of liquid beverage enhancers, addressing health&nbsp;&amp; wellness needs through the reformulation of existing products and introduction of new products, and investing in world-class marketing. Increased advertising in brands like
<I>Velveeta</I>, <I>Philadelphia</I>, <I>Kraft Mayo</I> and <I>Capri Sun</I> has already resulted in significant sales increases. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Lastly, Kraft Foods Group will <I>redefine efficiency</I> to free up cash, in order to make these important investments in people, innovation and marketing. The company will employ several tools such as
Lean Six Sigma, supply chain simplification and strategic sourcing, with the goal of becoming the lowest cost producer in its categories. Success will be measured through external benchmarking to reinforce a results-driven culture. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Long-term Outlook </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods Group expects to be well-positioned over the long term to deliver steady, reliable growth with a strong focus on cash flow to fund a highly competitive dividend and reinvestment in people,
innovation and brand-building. The company will consistently aim to accomplish: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Organic revenue
growth</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">1</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"> at or above the North American food and beverage
market rate of growth; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mid-single digit Operating Income growth; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mid-to-high single digit EPS growth; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mid-single digit dividend growth; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="9%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Free Cash
Flow</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">1</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"> of at least 85% of Net Income.
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;Cash will be king at Kraft,&#148; said Tim McLevish, Chief Financial Officer of Kraft Foods Group.
&#147;What matters to shareholders is total return and dollars in their pockets. And cash will be the fuel to grow our business.&#148; </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>2013 Outlook </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft
Foods Group will launch from a position of strength, having delivered four consecutive quarters of top- and bottom-line growth. In 2013, the company expects to continue that momentum with organic revenue growth in line with market growth, despite a
negative impact of 1 point due to product pruning. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Productivity improvements and overhead savings are expected to drive 2013
EPS of approximately $2.60 on a GAAP basis. This outlook assumes interest expense of approximately $520 million and an effective tax rate of 35 percent. The results for the year also include restructuring costs of about $240 million (or 26 cents per
share), compared to expected ongoing costs of about $125 million (or 14 cents per share) in a typical year. Free cash flow is expected to be about 70 percent of GAAP net income &#150; below the long-term target of at least 85 percent due to an extra
tax payment in 2013 of approximately $200 million. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The management team expects to recommend to the Board an annual dividend
of $2.00 per share. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">A live audio webcast of today&#146;s presentations, including slides, is available at
<U>www.kraftfoodsgroup.com</U>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:8px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:2px;border-bottom:0.5pt solid #000000;width:10%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">1</SUP>&nbsp;</FONT><FONT

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Please see discussion of Non-GAAP financial measures at the end of this press release. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>ABOUT KRAFT FOODS GROUP </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">On Oct. 1, 2012, Kraft Foods Group, Inc. will spin-off from its parent, Kraft Foods Inc. (NASDAQ: KFT). A major player in grocery, cheese, convenient meals, beverages and foodservice, Kraft Foods Group
will be one of the largest consumer packaged food and beverage companies in North America.&nbsp;With a broad portfolio of iconic brands including <I>Kraft, Maxwell House, Oscar Mayer, Planters </I>and<I> JELL-O</I>, Kraft Foods Group had 2011
revenue of $18.7 billion. Kraft Foods Group will trade on the NASDAQ stock exchange under the ticker symbol &#147;KRFT.&#148; </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Also on Oct. 1, Kraft Foods Inc. will change its name to Mondel&#275;z International, Inc., which will be a high-growth global snacks
company with annual revenue of approximately $36 billion and leading brands including <I>Cadbury</I>, <I>Jacobs</I>, <I>LU</I>, <I>Milka</I>, <I>Nabisco</I>, <I>Oreo</I>, <I>Tang</I> and <I>Trident.&nbsp;</I>Mondel&#275;z International will trade on
the NASDAQ stock exchange under the ticker symbol &#147;MDLZ.&#148; Visit <U>www.kraftfoodscompany.com</U> and <U>www.facebook.com/kraftfoodscorporate</U>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This press release contains a number of
forward-looking statements. The words &#147;plan,&#148; &#147;drive,&#148; &#147;build,&#148; &#147;can,&#148; &#147;will,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148; &#147;aim&#148; and similar expressions are intended to identify forward-looking statements.
Examples of forward-looking statements include, but are not limited to, statements regarding Kraft Foods Group&#146;s strategic plans, financial targets and long-term guidance, including revenue and operating income growth, EPS and margins; Kraft
Foods Group&#146;s future dividends; Kraft Foods Group&#146;s opportunities to improve profitability and generate cash; Kraft Foods Group&#146;s restructuring costs; the timing and completion of the spin-off of Kraft Foods Group; and Kraft Foods
Group&#146;s expectations and goals for efficiency and productivity, resource allocation, reinvestment in our business, sales execution, cash management, free cash flow, innovation and employee recruitment, compensation and investment. These
forward-looking statements involve risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond Kraft Foods Group&#146;s control, which could cause Kraft Foods Group&#146;s actual results to differ materially from those indicated in the forward-looking
statements. Please see Kraft Foods Group&#146;s risk factors, as they may be amended from time to time, set forth in its filings with the SEC, including Kraft Foods Group&#146;s Registration Statement on Form 10 filed with the SEC and subsequent
reports on Form 8-K. Kraft Foods Inc. and Kraft Foods Group each disclaims and does not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statement in this press release, except as required by applicable law or regulation. </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>NON-GAAP FINANCIAL MEASURES </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods Group reports its financial results in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States (&#147;GAAP&#148;). </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods Group&#146;s top-line measure is organic revenue, which excludes the impacts of related party transactions, divestitures,
currency and accounting calendar changes. The company uses organic revenue and corresponding metrics as non-GAAP financial measures. Management believes organic revenue better reflects the underlying growth from the ongoing activities of Kraft Foods
Group&#146;s business and provides improved comparability of results. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The company also uses free cash flow as a non-GAAP
financial measure. Free cash flow is defined as net cash provided by operating activities less capital expenditures. Management believes free cash flow shows the financial health of, and how efficiently we are running, the company. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Non-GAAP financial measures should be viewed in addition to, and not as an alternative for, the company&#146;s results prepared in
accordance with GAAP. In addition, the non-GAAP measures the company is using may differ from the non-GAAP measures used by other companies. </FONT></P>

<div style='position:absolute;left:486px;top:64px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>statements.</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:576px;top:64px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>The</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:611px;top:64px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>words</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:660px;top:64px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;plan,&#148;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:712px;top:64px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;drive,&#148;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:769px;top:64px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;build,&#148;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:824px;top:64px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;focus,&#148;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:83px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;manage,&#148;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:154px;top:83px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;can,&#148;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:201px;top:83px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;will,&#148;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:244px;top:83px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>&#147;expect&#148;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:307px;top:83px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>and similar expressions are intended to identify our forward&#45;looking
statements. </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:102px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>Examples of forward&#45;looking statements include, but are not
limited to, statements regarding our strategic plans,&nbsp; </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:122px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>financial
targets and long&#45;term guidance, including revenue and operating income growth, margins, EPS and </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>market</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:130px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>share;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:179px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>our</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:207px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>future</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:253px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>dividends;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:329px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>our</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:358px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>restructuring</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:451px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>costs;</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:498px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>our</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:526px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>opportunities</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:622px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>to</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:640px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>improve</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:702px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>profitability</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:783px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>and</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:815px;top:141px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>generate </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:160px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>cash; our plans to provide ongoing guidance; and our expectations and goals for
efficiency and productivity, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:179px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>resource allocation, reinvestment in our
business, input cost management, sales execution, cash management, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:198px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>free cash
flow, innovation and employee recruitment, compensation and investment. These forward&#45;looking </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:217px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>statements involve risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control,
and important factors that </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:237px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>could cause actual results to differ materially
from those indicated in the forward&#45;looking statements include, but </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:256px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>are
not limited to, increased competition; continued consumer weakness and weakness in economic conditions; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:275px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>our ability to differentiate our products from retailer and economy brands; our
ability to maintain our reputation </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:294px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>and brand image; continued volatility of,
and sharp increases in, commodity and other input costs; pricing actions; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:313px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>increased costs of sales; regulatory or legal changes, restrictions or actions;
unanticipated expenses and </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:332px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>business disruptions; product recalls and product
liability claims; unexpected safety or manufacturing issues; our </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:352px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>indebtedness and our ability to pay our indebtedness; our inability to protect our
intellectual property rights; and </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:371px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>tax law changes. For additional
information on these and other factors that could affect our forward&#45;looking </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:390px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>statements, see our risk factors, as they may be amended from time to time, set
forth in our filings with the SEC, </div> <div style='position:absolute;left:77px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>including</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:144px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>our</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:173px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>Registration</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:263px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>Statement</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:341px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>on</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:364px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>Form</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:406px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>10.</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:434px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>We</div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:463px;top:409px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:16px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>disclaim</div>
